section.t:
This document uses key terminology from several sources:

        terms for the GEOPRIV reference model defined in ;

        the term Location Information Server (LIS), from , is a node in the access network that provides location information to an end point; a LIS provides location URIs;

        the term Location Server (LS), from , is used to identify the role that responds to a location dereference request; this might be the same entity as the LIS, but the model in  allows for the existence of separate - but related - entities; and

        the term location URI is coined in .
